  alert("Clicked!")
})




 7ï¸âƒ£ Regular Expressions (Regex)

Regex is used for pattern matching.

 ğŸ”¹ Syntax

js
/pattern/flags


 ğŸ”¹ Common Flags

| Flag | Meaning          |
| - | - |
| `g`  | global           |
| `i`  | case-insensitive |
| `m`  | multiline        |



 ğŸ”¹ Examples

 Check if string contains "cat"

js
/cat/.test("my cat")  // true




 Match digits

js
"abc123".match(/\d+/)
// ["123"]




 Email Validation (basic)

js
let emailRegex = /^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/
emailRegex.test("test@gmail.com")




 Non-Greedy Match (like your earlier doubt)

js
"a123t a45t".match(/a.+?t/g)
// ["a123t", "a45t"]


